## 2D Side-Scrolling Platformer Project Standards

### Project Type
This is a **2D Side-Scrolling Platformer** game developed using Unity 2D systems.

### Coordinate System
- **X-Axis**: Horizontal direction (left/right movement)
- **Y-Axis**: Vertical direction (up/down movement, jumping, gravity)
- **Z-Axis**: Typically used for depth sorting (Sorting Layer/Order), not for gameplay logic movement
- Default coordinate system: X positive to the right, Y positive upward

### 2D Component Usage Standards
- **Physics System**: Use `Rigidbody2D` and `Collider2D` (not 3D versions)
  - `Rigidbody2D` for physics movement
  - `Collider2D` (BoxCollider2D, CircleCollider2D, etc.) for collision detection
  - Use `Physics2D` API for 2D physics queries

- **Rendering System**: Use `SpriteRenderer` to render 2D sprites
  - Use `SortingLayer` and `SortingOrder` to control render order
  - Use `Sprite` assets instead of 3D Meshes

- **Camera**: Use `Camera` in `orthographic` mode
  - Set `orthographicSize` to control field of view
  - Camera typically follows the player along the X-axis

### Movement and Physics Standards
- **2D Movement**: Only consider X and Y axes
  ```csharp
  // ✅ Correct: 2D movement
  Vector2 position = new Vector2(x, y);
  transform.position = new Vector3(position.x, position.y, transform.position.z); // Z remains unchanged
  
  // ❌ Wrong: Using 3D movement
  transform.position += Vector3.forward * speed; // Should not use Z-axis movement
  ```

- **Direction Calculation**: Use `Mathf.Atan2` to calculate 2D angles
  ```csharp
  // ✅ Correct: 2D direction
  Vector2 direction = target - current;
  float angle = Mathf.Atan2(direction.y, direction.x) * Mathf.Rad2Deg;
  transform.rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0f, 0f, angle);
  ```

- **Distance Calculation**: Use `Vector2.Distance` or `Vector2.magnitude`
  ```csharp
  // ✅ Correct: 2D distance
  float distance = Vector2.Distance(pos1, pos2);
  // or
  float distance = (pos2 - pos1).magnitude;
  ```

### Collision Detection Standards
- Use `OnTriggerEnter2D`, `OnTriggerExit2D`, `OnCollisionEnter2D` and other 2D collision callbacks
- Use `Physics2D.Raycast`, `Physics2D.OverlapCircle` and other 2D physics queries
- Avoid using 3D physics APIs (such as `Physics.Raycast`)

### Animation and Tweening
- Use **DOTween** for animation and tweening
- 2D movement animations only manipulate X and Y coordinates
- Rotation animations only manipulate Z-axis (2D rotation)

### Code Examples
```csharp
// ✅ Correct: 2D platformer movement script
public class PlatformerMovement : MonoBehaviour
{
    private Rigidbody2D rb;
    private SpriteRenderer spriteRenderer;
    
    void Start()
    {
        rb = GetComponent<Rigidbody2D>();
        spriteRenderer = GetComponent<SpriteRenderer>();
    }
    
    void Update()
    {
        // 2D movement: only consider X-axis
        float moveX = Input.GetAxisRaw("Horizontal");
        rb.velocity = new Vector2(moveX * speed, rb.velocity.y);
        
        // 2D direction: flip Sprite
        if (moveX > 0)
            spriteRenderer.flipX = false;
        else if (moveX < 0)
            spriteRenderer.flipX = true;
    }
}

// ✅ Correct: 2D collision detection
void OnTriggerEnter2D(Collider2D collision)
{
    // 2D collision handling
}

// ❌ Wrong: Using 3D physics
void OnTriggerEnter(Collider collision) // Wrong! Should use Collider2D
{
}
```

### Important Notes
- All gameplay logic movement only uses X and Y axes
- Z-axis is only used for render sorting, not for gameplay logic
- Use 2D physics components and APIs
- Camera uses orthographic projection
- Sprite assets are used for visual representation
